definitions.definition: In what way; to what extent.
examples: It must be, what , twenty-five years since we first met.

definitions.definition: Used before a prepositional phrase to emphasise that something is taken into consideration as a cause or reason; usually used in combination with 'with' (see what with ), and much less commonly with other prepositions.

main_definition: ( interrogative ) In what way; to what extent.
secondary_definitions: Used before a prepositional phrase to emphasise that something is taken into consideration as a cause or reason; usually used in combination with 'with' (see what with ), and much less commonly with other prepositions.
